Valid commands (cAsE sEnSiTiVe, minimal sanity checking, one per line) are:
.
help (re-display this information)
ther[mostat][ a[uto]/ o[ff]/ h[eat]/ c[ool]] (to read or set thermostat)
fan[ a[uto]/ o[n]] (to read or set fan)
<pin number> set pin [to] output (or ...pin set)
<pin number> set pin [to] input [pers] (or ...pin set...) optional persistence
<pin number> set pin [to] input with pullup [pers] (or ...pin set...) optional persistence
<pin number> read pin (or ...pin read...)(obtain the name if any, setting and voltage)
read pins (or pins read )(obtain the names, settings and voltages of ALL pins)
<pin number> set pin [to] low [pers] (or ...pin set...)(only allowed to pins assigned as output) optional persistence
<pin number> set pin [to] high [pers] (or ...pin set...)(only allowed to pins assigned as output) optional persistence
<°C> set lower furnace temp (to turn furnace on at any lower temperature than this, always persistent)
<°C> set upper furnace temp (to turn furnace off at any higher temperature than this, always persistent)
talkback[ on/off] (or logging on/off)
talkback temp change[s[ on/off]] (or logging temp changes on/off)(requires normal talkback on)
report master room temp
power cycle (or cycle power)
ch[ange] pers[istent memory] <address> <value>
ch[ange] pers[istent memory] <StartingAddress> "<character string>["[ 0]] (store character string as long as desired, optional null-terminated. Reminder: echo -e and escape the quote[s])
vi[ew] pers[istent memory] <StartingAddress>[ <EndingAddress>]
vi[ew] fact[ory defaults] (so you can see what would happen before you reset to them)(not available with WeMo XI due to lack of memory space)
reset (factory defaults: pure, simple and absolute)
test alert (sends an alert message to host for testing purposes)
dht pin <pin number> (retrieves DHT device reading, a period with due care in place of pin number for all pins)
